< Name>
Kia Vang</Name>
<Time>1510442631691</Time><rating>5< /rating>< Text>
I had been needing some work done on my molar teeth due to some decay. I was just passing by when I saw their sign that caught my attention, "Dental Walk-In, Welcome." Of course, with any walk-in appointment, the wait time can last awhile. But, hey, they were happy to squeeze me into their busy schedule so I gladly waited.

Everyone from the front end office to the staff in the back office was super friendly and professional. I love their hospitality. I was offered water, tea, and coffee by several different staff during my visit. while I waited in the treatment room, I was given the TV remote! I had my very own TV screen to watch. I felt very comfortable and at ease.

I had the pleasure of being Dr. Nguyen patient. He took very great care of me and took his time treating my teeth. During my treatment, I was given shades to wear so the bright light above wouldn't hurt my eyes. That was very thoughtful and made a huge difference. After treating my teeth and filling it, my teeth look so natural and beautiful.

I have to mention that I don't have dental insurance so I paid out of pocket with my own money. They do offer a great dental plan for patients like me who don't have their own dental insurance. It's a great investment, two cleanings, two exams, one complete x-ray, and 20% off all treatment. Now there's more to that dental insurance, I only wrote what caught my eyes and interest. Sadly, I didn't do the math and realized it later that it would have been better to pay an additional money to get their dental plan and save more money for my future treatment. Their dental plan would have covered the limited exam I received that day AND I would have received the 20% off for my treatment. Yeah, so I'm really kicking myself now for now realizing this sooner. When you're a single mom and working part-time, you need to budget better.

I do plan to go back and get more treatment done and purchase the dental plan.

Some other things I like to mention before ending my review:
-the restroom was very clean and offered mouthwash, toothbrushes, and toothpaste.
-the whole facility was clean and had great decorations and family portraits.
-I loved how I was able to lay down and watch TV while getting my teeth treated. It was a great way to distract my mind so I wasn't terrified.
-I liked how the back office offered lip balm and floss key chains to patients.
-AND most importantly, I didn't know I was Dr. Nguyen last patient for the day until I was paying for my treatment and overheard him talking about his plans for the evening now that he was off. Usually, you get the dreaded attitude because the doctor just wants to go home. But Dr. Nguyen was the complete opposite. He really took his time to take care of me. He didn't rush through the procedure. He was in full spirit and was outgoing. We talked and laugh throughout my procedure. AND I WAS HIS LAST PATIENT. He really is passionate about his work and patient. And made a great impression on me.<//Text>

< review>
I've been going to Shinano's for longer than I can remember. Great food. Great atmosphere. My family has always typically ordered one of their "Boats", a combination of meats (beef, chicken, salmon), mixed tempura, sushi, sashimi, and fruit served on a large wooden boat. Along with the boat comes rice, miso soup, and tsukemono. It is a feast!

When it's busy, servers can tend to forget you, but luckily you'll have plenty of food to keep you occupied.</review>

<rate>2</rate><response>None</response>< review>
I really like the employees there they have always been very nice. I had been going to Philly's for 2 years now, and had not  gone to any other nail salon. I had to stop going a couple of months ago because I noticed a strange discoloring of my toenails, the young lady didn't say anything but it alarmed me.....so I took the nail polish off after a week to check it out and realized I had the beginning of a fungus on my toenails.I believe that maybe their practices may not be a strict as they need to be. I am now treating my toes and think I caught it before it got too horrible. Only one toenail has lifted from my toe bed.I have never had a fungus before or have any issues with my feet. So after my toes clear up completely I will do a little bit of research on how often they clean or change out files etc.. before I go back to a nail salon again.</review>

<review>I am really pleased with the new management of this place. My only experience with the previous management was a large catering order that went horribly wrong - it arrived 2 hours late and with half the food missing. Luckily the bill was fixed to reflect that but since this was for our "welcome to our new office" party it was a huge disappointment and I had fully sworn the place off for anything in the future. Once I found out they were under new management, I decided to give them a whirl personally. The fish tacos are quite good and I do appreciate the option of mixing and matching which tacos I want to try. The build your own bowl is a cool option as well since I can personalize what I want. There aren't a ton of vegetarian options so personalizing is basically the only way to go. The food is kinda expensive for a normal work lunch so it's not someplace I go often. They offer Mexican coke in the bottle which I love and the staff is always very friendly and patient. The guacamole is absolutely one of the best I've ever had anywhere which will keep me coming back. :)</review><Resp>None</Resp><Date>1518550076153</Date></record>

<rate>5</rate><Text>Un Mondo is a great contemporary twist on delicious Mexican food. The atmosphere is very clean and upbeat with a great system set up on how to order your food. How you order is you walk in and there's three big menus set up on the wall with cards below them to fill out on how exactly you want your food (just like Which Which). Then you take it to the person at the counter. And then take a seat and they will bring it to you in a jiffy.

The staff is Awesome as well. The owner is super friendly and informative. April who is at the counter is the best, super sweet and makes sure you are doing alright and you're happy with everything.

Lastly the food is bomb! Make sure to try all the salsas too :)<//Text><pics>None< /pics><resp>None</resp>< gmapID>

<Review>It's a nice California-style taco place, I came by for their Taco Tuesday.

They don't advertise it at all as far as I can see, but they offered carnitas tacos and pastor tacos, both for $1.50 each on Taco Tuesday.

Maybe it's because I went in late-ish at 8:30pm, but they are the slowest taco place I have ever been to before. There weren't too many people in there, maybe half the seats were empty, but they took 15-20 minutes to prepare each order.

Also, looking around, everyone's orders were rife with errors. For-here orders became to-go. My order sat around for a while because the cashier assumed I left for some reason until I asked. Some people got flags to put on their tables with their order numbers and some didn't. Pretty strange.

The pastor was unusual - it was literally just the pastor meat sitting on tortilla. However, they crisped up the meat really nicely, so it tasted good, particularly with the orange salsa, so I'm not sure I can complain. However, I wonder if that's how it was meant to come out or if they messed it up. I've never seen a bare taco like that before not at a place where you can add in fillings yourself.

The carnitas was also nicely crisped up. I think they messed up my order the first time around - I asked for 2 regular and 1 without cilantro, and all 3 came out with just bare meat and onions. I went back and ordered another and this time it was with onions and cilantro. I'm a little unclear whether the first one was the mistake, or the second one, but I assume with the cilantro is the way it was supposed to come. I like the flavor of the pastor better, but I preferred this one for having the accompaniments of onions and cilantro.

The food was good, and at a great price on Taco Tuesday, but it was a pretty weird experience how they seemed to screw up practically everything that could be screwed up.<//Review>< Rating>
4< /Rating>

<Pics>None</Pics><response>{'time': 1606780520161, 'text': 'Ron,\n\nWe appreciate patient feedback, even negative feedback, as it helps us better improve when needed. I do want to address the validity of your concerns in your review though.\nTo provide the best patient care possible, we employ back-office assistants with a range of licenses, including the highest license of RDA-EF2, which requires extended education from the dental assistant.  Each back-office assistant does what they are licensed to do. Dependent on the treatment needed, an RDA-EF2 may perform specific tasks within the scope of their license. We are proud to employ these dental assistants to ensure our patients receive optimal care.\nI am sorry to hear that you found one of our doctors‚Äô bedside manner to be rude. The doctor that you saw in our office has an extremely loyal patient base and many positive reviews. Your visit should have been no different and I apologize if that was not the case.\nIt is important to know that not all teeth that are in need of a crown are also in need of root canal treatment at the time. Our doctors would never diagnose or perform treatment until there is an indication that treatment is needed. Our crown preparation consent form does notify all patients that their crowned tooth may later need root canal treatment if the tooth becomes symptomatic. There are many factors out of our control that could lead to the root canal being needed later on. However, it is not the case that every crowned tooth later needs a root canal so it would be a disservice to prematurely perform the treatment.\nIn regards to your insurance, upon reviewing your chart I do see that we are in network with your insurance and that they did pay their percentage of coverage toward your treatment. The claim that your insurance dropped Capital Dental Group is undeniably false.  Each of our doctors are contracted, individually, to be in certain PPO networks and I can assure you that no dental network has ever dropped any of our doctors.\nWe never want a patient to have a poor experience in our office and we apologize if there was miscommunication on our part that lead to confusion and the result of your review. <rating>5<//rating><review>I had been having severe pain for almost a week and called all around to try and find somewhere to get me in but Capital Dental was the only place able to get me in same day. I had no insurance so opted for an extraction as I unfortunately could not afford to go the route of root canal. It still ended up costing a bit more then I would have hoped but I cannot say enough about the excellent care I received. I went into it nervous but ready to get some sort of relief. In my experience with dental work, the numbing is the worst part. Not this time! Dr. Patel was so gentle and always told me what to expect with each step he took (ex: you will feel a pinch here, you will feel pressure, etc). When actually extracting the tooth I felt no discomfort! I was actually quite surprised he was able to get it out so quickly and easily. He did say there was a small piece left behind but he got it out and even had them do another x-ray before I left just to make sure. The dental assistant that helped during the procedure was so friendly & sweet. She even helped wipe my eyes when they watered involuntarily lol. Also when the extraction started she grabbed my hands in an attempt to comfort me (I assume anyway lol). She told me her name right before I left but I have a horrible memory and completely forgot what it was. I really wish I remembered so she could receive the recognition she deserves. Overall my experience was better then I had expected & I will be recommending Capital Dental to people looking on the future!</review><pics>None< /pics>< Response>

I was referred to Capital Dental by a friend who does not have dental insurance - I figured they must be doing something right for anyone to pay cash for dental work! < rating>
5</rating>
< review>
I have been a patient for just under a year.  I came here because I received some bad advice from my former Dentist about receiving a crown instead of an implant years ago.  My crown broke, as they always do, and I needed to get an implant or walk around wearing a partial denture for the rest of my life...no thank you!  Dr. Richard "Chip" Casteen had to do a bone graft, put in an implant, then put on a temporary crown (while I get some much needed ortho), and I'll get the final crown in about 4-6 months.  There were some financial issues, as you can imagine, but they worked with me.  Trish, his Executive Assistant, worked with me to get things done.  Point blank these guys are awesome, and if you are getting an implant, there is no other place to go!  I live in LA, and I've made several trips up there to Bakersfield, and it was well worth it. Do yourself a favor, and don't go to the bargain center, go to Capital Dental Group.< /review>
